title._content: St. Patrick's Catholic Church Outside Atchison, Kansas, Is an Example of Native Stone Pioneer Architecture. The Parish Was Begun in a Log Church in 1857 by Benedictine Monks and Replaced by This Structure in 1865. It Is Still in Use Today 06/1974
